cs.CV, cs.DL, cs.GR, cs.HC, cs.MM

The paper discusses mathematical methods for digital image restoration and visualisation, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.DL) for image processing. The focus of the paper is on illuminated manuscripts, which fall under the category of graphics (cs.GR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) due to their historical and cultural significance. Finally, the paper also touches upon the use of digital restoration as a generic toolkit for the arts, which could potentially fall under multimedia (cs.MM).
